    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-05-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Canisius</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 57.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States of America</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Vienna</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 8, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:* * * * The news received here per telegraph that
                    you have demanded of Austria the discontinuation of sending any more volunteers
                    to Maximilian, of Mexico, has created here quite a sensation. The people of
                    Austria feel now, in their distress, more than ever, that this enterprise of
                    Maximilian, and the subsequent agreement made by this government to aid him by
                    sending soldiers to that distant country, of no value to the people of this
                    empire, was a great mistake.</p>
                <p>I found in this morning’s paper the following item:</p>
                <pb facs="0926" n="844" xml:id="pg_844"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>[Translation.]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">“Laybach</hi>, (near Trieste,) <hi rend="italic"
                                >May</hi> 5.</placeName>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">“The Mexican free corps</hi>.—The recruiting for the
                        Mexican free corps will definitely be closed to-day. All the recruits have
                        to be ready on the 8th of this month at the principal depot at Laybach, as
                        the embarcation commences in Trieste on the 10th instant. The Mexican
                        Colonel Leisser will personally attend to the embarcation.”</p>
                    <p>What the Austrian government will decide now, after your protest, will soon
                        he seen, as the embarcation was to take place on the 10th of this month.</p>
                    <p>I have the honor to be, very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>T. CANISIUS, <hi rend="italic">United States Consul</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Secretary of State.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
